messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /api/articles/{slug}

All methods acceptable:
- false

Methods (based on code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In main (hello.go) the top-level router group is created as v1 := r.Group("/api").
- The articles routes are mounted on v1.Group("/articles"). So the ArticlesRegister / ArticlesAnonymousRegister handlers are under the prefix /api/articles.
- ArticleUpdate is registered in articles.ArticlesRegister as router.PUT("/:slug", ArticleUpdate). That yields the PUT method on path /api/articles/:slug → represented as /api/articles/{slug}.
- The same path also has other handlers registered elsewhere in the same group:
  - ArticlesAnonymousRegister registers router.GET("/:slug", ArticleRetrieve) → GET /api/articles/{slug}.
  - ArticlesRegister also registers router.DELETE("/:slug", ArticleDelete) → DELETE /api/articles/{slug}.
- There is no router.Any or router.Any-like registration, so "all methods" is false.
- The code does not explicitly register HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, or PATCH handlers for the path, so those methods are considered not acceptable based on the code (even though some servers/frameworks may implicitly handle HEAD).
